  "notes": "Proto-Germanic (~500 BCE – 1st c. CE). Reconstructed common ancestor of all Germanic languages. Defining innovation: Grimm's Law (*p→*f, *t→*θ, *k→*x; *b→*p, *d→*t, *g→*k; *bʰ→*β, *dʰ→*ð, *gʰ→*ɣ) + Verner's Law. Fixed initial stress accent. PIE *o→*a merger. *ɸ (bilabial) at this stage, not yet [f]. Source: Ringe (2006), Kroonen (2013).",
